==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stagworm
<hw>Stag"worm`</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧g"w⟦ucir⟧rm`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The larva of any species of botfly which is
parasitic upon the stag, such as <spn>Oestrus actaeon</spn>, or
<spn>Hypoderma actaeon</spn>, which burrows beneath the skin, and
<spn>Cephalomyia auribarbis</spn>, which lives in the
nostrils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stagy</ent>⟦br⟧
